I tried to fix the error by adding the following line to the top of org.eclipse.cosmos.rm.smlif.internal.editor.SMLIFEditor.getDocumentNode() :

		if ((workspaceFile != null) && (!workspaceFile.exists()))
			return null;

This moves things along a little farther, but then I get an infinite number of error dialogs that say "An error has occurred.  See error long for more details.".  The error log doesn't really provide any useful information in this case.

I had also tried adding a case for IResourceChangeEvent.PRE_DELETE in the resource change listener, and I tried looking for event.getDelta().getKind() to equal a removal.  But the infinite error message box problem occurs before we even get to those cases.  Ali, do you have any ideas on this?
